to attain/to reach/to amount to/to communicate/eminent

sentences.english: It is inter-dynamic that the developed country has already formed the supplementary pension and capital market.
sentences.chinese: 发达国家已经形成了企业年金与资本市场的良性互动。

sentences.english: and strong demands from China for the transfer of technology from the rich to others.
sentences.chinese: 中国强烈要求发达国家将相关技术引进其它地区。

sentences.english: The United States is on the list at no. 31, behind eight other developing countries.
sentences.chinese: 美国排在31名，在其它8个发达国家的后面。

sentences.english: Through research, we sum up practices and experiences cold-chain food logistics of developed country.
sentences.chinese: 发达国家在这方面有许多值得学习和借鉴的经验。

sentences.english: Emerging economies, in general, have fewer automatic stabilisers than rich ones do.
sentences.chinese: 新兴经济体的财政自动稳定器普遍弱于发达国家。

sentences.english: Developed nations should spare no effort to finance their economically disadvantaged counterparts.
sentences.chinese: 发达国家应该不遗余力地资助贫国。

sentences.english: This has easily offset the general decline in the birthrate of advanced countries.
sentences.chinese: 发达国家的出生率的普遍降低被轻易抵消。

sentences.english: The United States largely developed the ARPANET and its successor, the Internet.
sentences.chinese: 美国主要发达国家的阿帕网及其后继者，因特网。

sentences.english: Only developed nations, including the US, would be expected to guarantee cuts.

sentences.english: Homestay in developed countries already have decades of history.
sentences.chinese: 家庭寄宿在发达国家已经有了好几十年的历史。

sentences.english: The administration has delinked human rights from economic aid to under developed nations.
sentences.chinese: 政府已把人权问题与对不发达国家的经济援助脱钩。

sentences.english: For a long time debt in the rich world has grown faster than incomes.
sentences.chinese: 长期以来，发达国家的债务增长一直快于收入的增长。

sentences.english: will, it won't matter what the developed countries do.
sentences.chinese: 那么，发达国家无论做什么也是没有意义了。

sentences.english: We have the most crime among rich countries.
sentences.chinese: 我们在发达国家中有最多的犯罪。

sentences.english: Many marketing lists are developed by telemarketers but are quite expensive.
sentences.chinese: 许多发达国家的营销者名单，也相当昂贵的电话。

sentences.english: Europe, America and Japan, and other developed countries have their own gifts research institutions.
sentences.chinese: 欧美日等发达国家都有自己的礼赠品研究机构。
